With regard to the dorsal chromatic pattern, the blue background colour of the pronotum, in most specimens shows green reflections (
Fig. 1
). The dark discal spots are always connected to the dark anterolateral area. The background colour of the elytra is usually carmine red, and may be more or less bright. The large dark discal macula, has a tinge that ranges from greenish to violet, and can slightly vary in extension, thus giving the specimen a more or less dark aspect. In some specimens from Sicily, this macula can be very faint or occasionally totally absent, but in this case the red background colour turns to violet or to a rather dull orange (
Fig. 56
).
